My very dear friend Katie Jones 21 years old and was diagnosed with breast cancer this past September .

TID: She underwent surgery at the end of June to remove the cancer, which was successful. But, with further testing cancerous cells were detected in her lymph nodes. As a result, she will be having to undergo 4 months of chemothearapy starting July 26 th, followed by weeks of radition.

Because of this, she has been unable to work and will likely not be able to return until the Fall. Some of her medical expenses are not covered and with the everyday necessities of life, money is getting tighter and tighter.
Katie Jones is one of the strongest, most selfless people I have ever known and is always there to give her love and support or the shirt off her back to anyone that needs it.
Now, it's time that we send back some of that love and support to Katie. Anything you can donate will be truly appreciated. Please spread the word. Thank you from the bottom of our hearts.

My fiancee, Sam, was in a horrific wreck on Wednesday, June 23,2021. He lost control and wrecked on a winding highway road with faster speeds, sending his truck flying and then rolling down the pavement. It was absolutely an accident that one would expect a fatality from. Yet, he only suffered a chest contusion and fractured ribs, a concussion, and several cuts that required stitches. He is lucky to be alive and I am so beyond grateful that he is. However, due to the aftereffects of the chest contusion, he is out of work for 2 weeks. This wouldn't be so bad, except his hours have already been drastically reduced due to COVID-19. EVENT_TITLE: This Boy Need Medice To Save His Life
EVENT_DESCRIPTION: The miracle treatment that should have saved Becka Boscarino's baby almost kills him.

TID: Doctors diagnosed their newborn son Magglio with Pompe disease, which is a very rare and fatal genetic condition because it causes the accumulation of glycogen in the body. If he was not treated, the baby would likely die before his first birthday.
There is only one treatment: a series of infusions. But after the boy received the fifth dose of it, he turned blue, stopped breathing, and fell into anaphylactic shock.

Doctors discovered that Magglio's body produced antibodies to the drug that was saving his life. It is a problem that few patients and doctors know about; in reality, the phenomenon has not been systematically studied. However, experts say that has happened to many patients taking other drugs.
The immune system produces antibodies, blood proteins that attack molecules that the body recognizes as foreign and that are often carried by viruses and bacteria. But antibodies are also deployed

EVENT_DESCRIPTION: At weareSAD we help those with mental, emotional, social, and physical trauma. We are a rebirthed family filled with powerful spirits and wisdom, gained from our personal experiences. We passionately want to help break these chains and generational curses in order to heal our brothers and sisters of all ages, cultural, genders, and backgrounds! In order to restore peace within the nation, let alone community, it begins with self. Yet many have literally been alone in this world mentally, they don’t even know how to begin, and many don’t have anyone to even teach them the steps. Here we understand those with thoughts that may be too extreme to others or yet your mind wants to know why, those with deep mental illnesses that others misjudge, those that went thru sexual trauma and battle with erratic thoughts, those that cry and battle with depression while others call them demons, etc. I come without a degree, yet we all come from experience, and grew from pain, so join me in healing."

EVENT_TITLE: Help A Passionate Premed Apply to Medical School
EVENT_DESCRIPTION: Hello, my name is Sharon and I am a graduate from the University of Oregon in Human Physiology. I am working on saving up the money to apply to medical school - which by myself will take 4-5 years. It may come as a surprise but applying for medical school is a very expensive endeavor between primary & secondary applications, interviews, etc. I have loved medicine my entire life and I have an incredible passion for helping people. I am a volunteer firefighter and I plan on beginning my medical career as a medical corps officer in the Navy. I have huge aspirations to make this world a better place, yet money has always held me back. If you can help at all, no matter the amount, or even by sharing, it is GREATLY appreciated.
